<p>I am taking a web page authoring class for school and I can't seem to solve a problem with the web page I'm building.</p>  <p>I have my navigation bar inside the header of my web page. </p>  <p>The heading is three words with the two on the outside using one font and the middle word using another font; all using 'span class'. </p>  <p>For my navigation bar the same font is being used for the list items that make up the two outside words of the header.The font only renders correctly in the navbar when I remove the font size. </p>  <p>However, <em>this makes the font small and I want to enlarge it.</em> </p>  <p>When I add in the font size, the page renders the second in line font while still maintaining all the font properties. </p>  <p>I don't understand what is going on. This has been driving me nuts for hours. </p>  <p><strong><em>The problem is in the style style sheet.</em></strong></p>  <p>If anyone also has any pointers for me too, that would be much appreciated.</p>  <p>EDIT: <a href="http://jsbin.com/sofitu/edit?html,css" rel="nofollow">Here's a working link for my Project a JS Bin</a></p>  <p>However, the header_image is no longer showing. ? </p>  <p><strong>-- Style CSS --</strong></p>  <pre><code>@font-face {     font-family: Exo;     src: url("/Macintosh\ HD\ 1/Library/Fonts/Converted\ Fonts/Exo.eot");     src: url("/Macintosh\ HD\ 1/Library/Fonts/Converted\ Fonts/Exo.svg") format("svg"),           url("/Macintosh\ HD\ 1/Library/Fonts/CustomFonts_WebFonts/Exo.ttf") format("truetype"), } @font-face {     font-family: "Calvin and Hobbes";     src: url("/Macintosh\ HD\ 1/Library/Fonts/CustomFonts_WebsFonts/CalvinandHobbes.ttf")           format("truetype"); }  /* Body Styles */  body {     background-image: url("/Volumes/Atlas/Anjreu\ Theodore\'s\ Documents/Computer\ Science/Web\ Development/LabelWebsite\:FiveFingerPrints/mycomputer_draft2/images/fiveFingerPrintsDark.png");     background-attachment: fixed;     background-postion: center center;     back